    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nWe exist to improve Engineering \u0026 Product leaders’ understanding and decision-making on how to efficiently and effectively manage Snowflake’s R\u0026D business. Our North Star is to provide trusted partnership via sharing of reliable metrics, inferring actionable insights, catalyzing strategic investment decisions and accelerating operational efficiency across R\u0026D and Finance.\n\nOur team operates at the intersection of strategy, finance, and R\u0026D execution - partnering closely with Engineering \u0026 Product, Technical Program Management, Corporate Finance, Corporate Development, Human Resources, Recruiting and Snowflake’s Executive Leadership to ensure that R\u0026D investments are efficient, effective and aligned to Snowflake’s growth priorities.\n\nThis is an early-in-career role supporting the Product Finance team, offering hands-on exposure to financial planning, analysis, and business partnership with a fast-paced R\u0026D organization. You will help maintain forecasts and analyze performance across product lines and initiatives. We are looking for someone who is detail-oriented, eager to learn and motivated to build strong business fundamentals and acumen.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO:\n\nThis role will support recurring reporting, own budgeting variance analyses, and help translate data into actionable, clear insights for R\u0026D stakeholders. You will collaborate closely with senior analysts and cross-functional partners, developing the skills to navigate ambiguity, ask thoughtful questions, and continuously improve processes. This role is ideal for a proactive self-starter with strong analytical curiosity who wants to grow into a strategic finance partner over time.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL NEED:\n\n - Bachelor’s Degree: In Finance, Economics, Data Science, Computer Science, or a related field\n\n - 1-3 years of experience: background in Finance, Investment Banking, Consulting, Accounting\n\n - Ability to translate complex data into clear, actionable insights for stakeholders at all levels\n\n - Proven ability in financial modeling, forecasting, and data analysis to support strategic decision making\n\n - Strong sense of accountability with a proactive, solutions-oriented approach to learning, improving, and driving work forward\n\n - AI competency and familiarity - uses AI solutions as tools to automate manual, recurring processes and deliverables\n\n - Prior cloud-based or SaaS company experience is a plus:\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
